Name: Mariano Díaz Mejía
Number: 24
Position: Forward
Goals: 0
Assists: 1

Mariano Díaz Mejía (Spanish pronunciation: [maˈɾjano ˈði.að meˈxi.a];[α] born 1 August 1993), 
known as Mariano, is a professional footballer who plays as a striker for La Liga club Real Madrid.
Shortly after making his debut for Badalona in 2011, Mariano joined Real Madrid, where he played in 
the C-team and then the reserves, where he was top scorer in the 2015–16 Segunda División B. He then 
began playing with the first team, and was part of their squad that won La Liga, the UEFA Champions 
League and the FIFA Club World Cup in 2016–17. He was subsequently signed by Ligue 1 club Olympique 
Lyonnais but returned to Madrid one year later.
